import React, { Component } from "react"; import $ from "jquery"; import Vague from "vague"; export default class Blurback extends Component { componentDidMount() { var hgt = $("#container"), bgt = $("#container .revealPic"); var bgtHalfW = bgt.width() / 2, bgtHalfH = bgt.height() / 2; /**Change position of .revealPic and background-image within it on mousemove over container**/ hgt.mousemove(function(event) { event.preventDefault(); bgt.show(); var scrollLeftPos = $(window).scrollLeft(), scrollTopPos = $(window).scrollTop(), offsetLft = hgt.offset().left, offsetTp = hgt.offset().top; var upX = event.clientX; var upY = event.clientY; bgt.css({ backgroundPosition: "" + (offsetLft - upX + bgtHalfW - scrollLeftPos) + "px " + (offsetTp - upY + bgtHalfH - scrollTopPos) + "px", top: "" + (-offsetTp + upY - bgtHalfH + scrollTopPos) + "px", left: "" + (-offsetLft + upX - bgtHalfW + scrollLeftPos) + "px" }); }); /*********************************************/ /*Hide .revealPic div on mouseout*/ hgt.mouseout(function() { bgt.hide(); }); /*********************************/ /*Using vague.js to make blurred image*/ var vague = $("#container img").Vague({ intensity: 10 }); vague.blur(); } render() { return (
